comment: Johnson (DET) and James (CLE) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Harris (DET) and Love (CLE) briefly engage during rebounding.
Jackson (DET) and Dellavedova (CLE) make incidental contact with one another as they dive for the loose ball.
LHH shows that Jackson (DET) hooks James's (CLE) arm and affects his RSBQ at the start of his spin move.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) sets the screen on Thompson (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Morris (DET) firms up as he sets the screen on Thompson (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Johnson (DET) trips Irving (CLE) and affects his RSBQ.
Jackson (DET) legally contests Irving's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Irving (CLE) was behind the three point line on his field goal was upheld.
Dellavedova (CLE) sets the screen on Caldwell-Pope (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jackson (DET) makes body contact with Irving (CLE) that affects his RSBQ.
Irving (CLE) makes incidental contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his ability to defend.
Thompson (CLE) and Morris (DET) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Irving (CLE) makes incidental contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Irving (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his RSBQ.

Irving (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and makes no contact with Jackson (DET) as he initially reaches in for the steal. Jackson then initiates contact with Irving as he jumps sideways on his shot attempt.
